Reasoning: The paper discusses the convergence of Compressive Sampling Matching Pursuit (CoSaMP) and Subspace Pursuit (SP) algorithms for compressive sensing, which are commonly studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT), Signal Processing (cs.SP), Numerical Analysis (cs.NA), and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper presents new results for CoSaMP, which may also be of interest to researchers in the Sparse and Low-rank Modeling (cs.SI) sub-category.
